# Playbook Component Props Reference

> **Parent rule:** See `frontend-development.mdc` for component selection, spacing tokens, styling priorities, and React vs ERB naming.

Curated reference of commonly used Playbook components and their key props.
Skip `dark`, `className`, `id`, `aria`, `data`, `htmlOptions` — those are always available.

---

## Layout

### Flex
Flexbox container — primary layout tool.

| Prop | Values | Default | Notes |
|------|--------|---------|-------|
| orientation | `"row"`, `"column"` | `"row"` | Main axis direction |
| gap | `"xxs"`, `"xs"`, `"sm"`, `"md"`, `"lg"`, `"xl"`, `"none"` | `"none"` | Space between children |
| align | `"start"`, `"center"`, `"end"`, `"stretch"`, `"baseline"` | `"none"` | Cross-axis alignment |
| justify | `"start"`, `"center"`, `"end"`, `"around"`, `"between"`, `"evenly"` | `"none"` | Main-axis distribution. Figma specs emit `"spaceBetween"` — convert to `"between"` |
| wrap | `boolean` | `false` | Allow children to wrap |
| inline | `boolean` | `false` | Inline-flex display |
| reverse | `boolean` | `false` | Reverse child order |

### FlexItem
Dedicated flex child wrapper. Use only when no other Playbook component wraps the content.
The `flex` global prop can be applied directly to any component — `FlexItem` is not required for flex sizing.

| Prop | Values | Default | Notes |
|------|--------|---------|-------|
| grow | `boolean` | `false` | Allow item to grow (`flex-grow: 1`) |
| shrink | `boolean` | `false` | Allow item to shrink (`flex-shrink: 1`) |
| fixedSize | `string` | — | Fixed width/height (e.g., `"250px"`) |
| overflow | `"auto"`, `"hidden"`, `"scroll"`, `"visible"` | — | Overflow behavior |

**Note:** Use the `flex` **global prop** (e.g., `flex="3"`) on any component for proportional sizing.
React: `<FlexItem>` / ERB: `pb_rails("flex/flex_item")`.

### Card
Elevated content container with border and shadow.

| Prop | Values | Default | Notes |
|------|--------|---------|-------|
| padding | `"none"`, `"xxs"`, `"xs"`, `"sm"`, `"md"`, `"lg"`, `"xl"` | `"md"` | Inner padding; use `"none"` for tables |
| borderRadius | `"xs"`, `"sm"`, `"md"`, `"lg"`, `"xl"`, `"none"`, `"rounded"` | `"md"` | Corner rounding |
| borderNone | `boolean` | `false` | Remove border entirely |
| selected | `boolean` | `false` | Blue left-border highlight |
| tag | `"div"`, `"section"`, `"footer"`, `"header"`, `"article"` | `"div"` | HTML element |

### Layout
Page-level layout with sidebar/body regions. Use sub-components `Layout.Side`, `Layout.Body`, `Layout.Header`.

### SectionSeparator
Horizontal or vertical divider between sections.

| Prop | Values | Default | Notes |
|------|--------|---------|-------|
| orientation | `"horizontal"`, `"vertical"` | `"horizontal"` | Line direction |
| lineStyle | `"solid"`, `"dashed"` | `"solid"` | Line style |
| variant | `"card"`, `"background"` | `"card"` | Visual weight |
| text | `string` | — | Optional label in the divider |

**Gotcha:** SectionSeparator renders at zero/minimal width by default. Always add `width="100%"` (React) or `width: "100%"` (ERB) so the line stretches to fill its container.

