## Forms

### TextInput

| Prop | Values | Default | Notes |
|------|--------|---------|-------|
| label | `string` | — | Always include a label |
| placeholder | `string` | — | Hint text |
| required | `boolean` | `false` | HTML form validation |
| requiredIndicator | `boolean` | `false` | Visual red asterisk (ERB: `required_indicator`). Use with `required` |
| disabled | `boolean` | `false` | Disabled state |
| error | `string` | — | Error message text |
| type | `"text"`, `"email"`, `"password"`, `"number"`, `"tel"`, `"url"` | `"text"` | Input type |

**Gotcha:** `required` and `requiredIndicator` are **different props**. `required` enables HTML5 validation. `requiredIndicator` shows the visual `*` asterisk. For Figma builds, the spec emits `requiredIndicator` — use that, not `required`.

### Textarea

| Prop | Values | Default | Notes |
|------|--------|---------|-------|
| label | `string` | — | Always include a label |
| placeholder | `string` | — | Hint text |
| rows | `number` | — | Visible rows; compute from Figma frame height |
| required | `boolean` | `false` | HTML form validation |
| requiredIndicator | `boolean` | `false` | Visual red asterisk (ERB: `required_indicator`). Use with `required` |
| disabled | `boolean` | `false` | Disabled state |
| error | `string` | — | Error message text |

**Gotcha:** Same as TextInput — `requiredIndicator` shows the `*`, `required` does validation. These are separate concerns.

